-- Pudong Development Bank, Sany Heavy, China Pacific: China Equities Preview
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-19T00:29:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/pudong-development-bank-sany-heavy-china-pacific-china-equities-preview.html
The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in China trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the close on Oct. 15.  The  Shanghai Composite Index , which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, declined 15.93, or 0.5 percent, to
2,955.23. The  CSI 300 Index  slid 0.7 percent to 3,306.16.  Mining companies: Copper gained for a second day, advancing
towards a 27-month high, as the dollar resumed a decline,
increasing the appeal of commodities as alternative investments.
The metal for three-month delivery on the London Metal Exchange
rose as much as 0.3 percent to $8,469 a metric ton by 8:02 a.m.
Singapore time.  Jiangxi Copper Co.  (600362 CH), China’s largest by market
value, fell 5.9 percent to 40.58 yuan.  Yunnan Copper Industry Co. 
(000878 CH) dropped 7.2 percent to 26.10 yuan.  Sany Heavy Industry Co.  (600031 CH) said its nine-month net
profit may have increased by as much as 130 percent to 4.56
billion yuan ($686.3 million) from the same period last year,
according to a filing on the Shanghai Stock Exchange yesterday.
Third-quarter earnings may have risen by 91 percent, it said.
The stock gained 4.1 percent to 35.24 yuan.  Shanghai Pudong Development Bank Co.  (600000 CH) plans to
raise 39.2 billion yuan in a private placement of 2.87 billion
shares at 13.75 yuan per share, the company said in a Shanghai
stock exchange filing yesterday. The stock rose 0.7 percent to
15.35 yuan.  China Sinoma International Engineering Co.  (600970 CH) said
nine-month net income may have risen as much as 90 percent as
sales increased as much as 50 percent, the company said in a
Shanghai stock exchange filing yesterday. The stock rose 2
percent to 35.29 yuan.  Xinjiang Ba Yi Iron & Steel Co.  (600581 CH) was profitable
in the third quarter after posting a net loss the same period a
year earlier, the company said in a Shanghai stock exchange
statement yesterday, citing estimated earnings. The stock jumped
3.7 percent to 13.88 yuan.  China Pacific Insurance (Group) Co.  (601601 CH) said its
nine-month premium income was 68.9 billion yuan for life and
39.1 billion yuan for property and casualty, according to a
filing to the Shanghai stock exchange yesterday. The stock fell
2 percent to 26.43 yuan.  Nanjing Iron & Steel Co.  (600282 CH) will increase the
valuation of a planned asset purchase to 9.09 billion yuan from
8.6 billion yuan, and will issue 2.19 billion shares, according
to a Hong Kong stock exchange filing yesterday. The stock gained
3.3 percent to 4.38 yuan.  China Railway Group Ltd.  (601390 CH) set the annual
interest payment for a debt issue at 4.34 percent for 10-year
bonds and 4.5 percent for 15-year bonds, the company said in a
Shanghai stock exchange statement yesterday. The stock rose 10
percent to 5.25 yuan.  -- Wang Ying  in Beijing. With assistance by Chua Kong Ho. Editor:
